# Customizable Quiz Application

## Project Description

This project is a flexible quiz application that allows users to test their knowledge across various topics. It leverages the Open Trivia Database (OpenTDB) to fetch quiz questions in real-time, offering a dynamic and personalized quiz experience.

## How to Play

1. **Choose Your Quiz**:
   - Visit the [OpenTDB API Configuration page](https://opentdb.com/api_config.php).
   - Select your preferred category, difficulty, and question type.
   - Copy the generated API URL.

2. **Retrieve Quiz Data**:
   - Open a new tab in your browser and paste the copied API URL.
   - The quiz data will be displayed in JSON format.

3. **Prepare the Quiz**:
   - Copy the list of questions from the JSON response.
   - Remove the `response_code` and `results` keys, keeping only the list of questions.

4. **Update the Project**:
   - Open the `data.py` file in your project directory.
   - Replace the existing data with the new list of questions.
   - Ensure the code is properly formatted and syntax is correct.

5. **Play**:
   - Run the application to enjoy your customized quiz!

## Features

- **Customizable Quizzes**: Choose from various topics, difficulty levels, and question types.
- **Real-time Data**: Fetch quiz questions directly from OpenTDB, ensuring up-to-date content.
- **Easy Setup**: Simple instructions to customize and play your quiz.

## Dependencies

- Python 3.x
- Requests (if fetching data programmatically)
- JSON (for data handling)

